Preheat #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{3}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (peeling optional). When boiling, add potatoes to the pot. Cook until fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Halve, peel and slice the @onion{1}(peeled and sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Cut the @broccoli{1}(cut into florets) into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

> If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Place a pan over medium-high heat (no oil).

When the pan is hot, add the @Irish beef mince{250%grams} and cook until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the onion to the mince (with a drizzle of @?oil{to taste} if needed) and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic, @tomato paste{1%pack} and @North Indian style spice mix{2%sachets} to the mince. Fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}, continuously stirring.

Stir in the @beef stock{1%sachet} and @water{150%ml}. Bring to the boil.

> Double the water for 4p.

Once boiling, reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and @sugar{to taste} and remove from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} and return to the pot off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste} and a splash of @?water{to taste} or @?milk{to taste}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.

When the filling is ready, transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Carefully layer the mash over the filling, using the back of a spoon to smooth it out. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden and bubbling, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Halfway through cooking, pop the broccoli onto a lined #baking tray{}. Toss together with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, salt and pepper. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast in the oven until tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When everything is ready, divide the curried cottage pie between your plates.

Serve the roasted broccoli alongside.